news.title: Once a year in July, there's a full 'Buck Moon'  --  here's what that means
news.summary: You may have caught the beautiful full moon on Tuesday night and heard it called the “Buck Moon.” That’s actually a name picked up from Native Americans, who referred to each month and full moon based on what was happening in the world around them.
